[1] Cholera - Angola (Huila)
Date: Thu, 19 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=481410>

At least 70 people died of cholera over the last 5 months in Angola's
southern Huila province, out of a total of 940 cases recorded in the
region, according to figures released by Lubango central Hospital.
This was revealed Thu, 19 Oct 2006, to Angop in Huila's capital city,
Lubango, by the acting head of the provincial health department, Felix
Januario, who said 763 have been discharged and 53 are still receiving
treatment in the hospital. He also noted that the new upsurge of 14 cases
since Sep 2006 is worrying the local sanitary authorities.
According to him, Government and its partners have installed 7 tents, and
are carrying out a sterilization campaign in the surroundings of Lubango,
to arrest the spread of the epidemics.
Meanwhile, the sanitary authorities have recorded 30 cases in the last 2
months in Quipungo district, resulting in the death of 10 people.
Since April 2006, Huila province has recorded a total of 1120 cases of
cholera that killed 101 persons.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
