[3] Cholera - Zambia (Central)
Date: Sat, 14 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Zambia Nationnal Broadcasting Corp [edited]
<http://www.znbc.co.zm/media/news/viewnews.cgi?category=13&id=1160845480>

Cholera has broken out at Waya fishing camp in the Lukanga swamps in
Central Province. Ministry of Health Spokesperson, Canisius Banda confirmed
the outbreak to ZNBC news.
Dr. Banda said 4 cases of cholera have been confirmed and that patients are
admitted to a cholera center in the area. He said of the 4 cholera
patients, 1 has been discharged.
Dr. Banda said the provincial Health office and the Kapiri Mposhi District
Health Management Team have put in place to measures to have the outbreak
under control. He said after consultations with the provincial Permanent
Secretary's office, the Ministry of Health has decided that the fishing
camp be closed immediately. Dr. Banda also said chlorine is being
distributed to communities to ensure their drinking water is clean.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
