[6] Cholera- Tanzania (Dar es Salaam)
Date: Tue, 17 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Souce: ReliefWeb [edited]
<http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/RWB.NSF/db900SID/KHII-6UN8HD?OpenDocument>

As for cholera, it was established that there were 42 patients still
recuperating at Mnyamani hospital out 60 who were admitted there in serious
condition during the weekend (14-15 Oct 2006).
Less than 15 percent of Dar es Salaam population of 4 million people have
access to pipe-borne water and the rest depend on water frequently vended
in unhygienic plastic paper bags and sold in unsanitary conditions. Cholera
has become endemic in the city. The perennial water crisis also affects
sewerage disposal. Over the past year, nearly 1000 cholera-related deaths
have been reported.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
