[7] Cholera - Nepal
Date: Sat, 14 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: People's Daily Online [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200610/14/eng20061014_311741.html>

At least 4 persons have died while more than 40 others have fallen ill
following an outbreak of cholera in Myagdi district in western Nepal, the
National News Agency, RSS, reported on Fri, 13 Oct 2006. According to the
RSS, the disease has spread in Takam village in the district due to food
contamination.
Villagers suspect that the disease spread across the village, some 400 km
west of Kathmandu, as a result of consuming meat of a sick buffalo during
the Dashain festival, the biggest festival in the country earlier this
month. Meanwhile, a medical team has been dispatched from the district
headquarters, Beni for the affected area, the report said.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
