[9] Dysentery - China (Sichuan)
Date: Fri, 13 Oct 2006
From: Dan Silver <dgsilver@yahoo.com>
Source: Xinhua [trans. by submitter] [edited]
<http://www.gmw.cn/content/2006-10/13/content_491956.htm>

Bacillary dysentery has broken out among over 100 students at Yuquan School
in Mianzhu City, Sichuan Province. A total of 143 students have symptoms of
illness. Since 10 Oct 2006, nausea, vomiting, abdominal pain, low fever,
diarrhea and other symptoms have appeared among students at Yuquan School
in Mianzhu City, and they have sought treatment at hospitals. On the
morning of 11 Oct 2006, Mianzhu City quickly put an emergency response plan
into action. The preliminary diagnosis is bacillary dysentery.
On the day of the outbreak, over 500 students ate at the school. A portion
of students who did not eat at the school have shown similar symptoms.
Relevant departments have obtained samples from the school cafeteria and
food stalls near the school. However, there is no trace of a few mobile
vendors who sold spicy soup nearby the school.
--
Dan Silver
<dgsilver@yahoo.com>
[Bacillary dysentery generally refers to shigellosis, as shown in the
outbreak below. A map of China showing the province of Sichuan can be
found at: <http://www.sichuangarden.com/image/specailty/china-map-g250.jpg>
ProMED thanks Dan Silver for this posting and the following one. - Mod.LL]
