[10] Shigellosis - China (Anhui)
Date: Mon, 16 Oct 2006
From: Dan Silver <dgsilver@yahoo.com>
Source: Xinhua [trans. by submitter] [edited]
<http://news.sina.com.cn/c/h/2006-10-16/000411243426.shtml>

On Sun, 15 Oct 2006, it was learned from Taihu County in Anqing City, Anhui
Province that bacillary dysentery was recently detected at Xincang Middle
School in Taihu County's Xincang Township. At the time of this writing,
34 students remained hospitalized. None are in critical
condition. Preliminary investigations indicate that the disease was caused
by students drinking unclean water.
According to the Anhui Provincial Health Bureau, on 13 Oct 2006 Xincang
Middle School discovered that some students had diarrhea. On the morning
of 14 Oct 2006, there was a gradual increase in students with diarrhea at
the school. The Taihu County Committee and county government immediately
put an emergency response plan into action. The school, township, and
hospital launched a thorough search. 100 students with similar symptoms
were examined in hospitals. Of these, 70 were admitted for treatment and
observation.
Anhui Province health departments are actively treating students who have
diarrhea; they have gathered samples of tap water at the school and stool
from students with diarrhea for lab analysis. _Shigella sonnei_ was
identified in the stool of patients. Total bacteria count and _E. coli_ in
the school's tap water exceed limits. At present all students with
diarrhea are undergoing active treatment. The health department provided
preventive medicine to those who are in close contact with the students.
[Byline: Dai Qun]
--
Dan Silver
<dgsilver@yahoo.com>
[A map of China's provinces showing the location of Anhui province in the
east-central part of the country can be found at:
<http://www.fas.usda.gov/pecad/remote/china/chinamap.gif> - Mod.LL]
